  {
    "title": "Science communication best practice: SlowMemo",
    "link": "https://www.cost.eu/science-communication-best-practice-slowmemo/",
    "pubDate": "2025-12-15T09:07:00.000Z",
    "content": "<html><head></head><body><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-self-guided-museum-activities-to-engage-with-our-past-and-present\">Self-guided museum activities to engage with our past and present</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Slow memory is an&nbsp;emergent concept that offers a new angle to reflect on how societies and individuals remember the pasts that&nbsp;meaningfully affects their present and future. It begins from the premise that we are familiar with commemorating sudden or extreme events such as wars, atrocities, or catastrophes but we are less certain about how to deal with&nbsp;slow-moving transformations that may be just as impactful. These slow transformations, such as climate change, deindustrialization, or structural racism, can have both negative and positive effects and occur often without a clear location or timeframe</p></body></html>",
